Previoud ticket is 00409909    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0BVijB:ref ]","techsupport@netwrix.com","Netwrix Support","atul.rathi@samsung.com","sumant.s@samsung.com; vinay.g@samsung.com; shakil.ahmad@samsung.com; nitin.patney@samsung.com","","true","2024-07-16T14:56:39.000Z","true"
Thank you for your time during the call today.
As mentioned, I will resend over the steps.
As proposed, leave the Audit Backup to run- soon, you should find some entries at the bottom of the page, with some tarball files of the logs.
1.You can download a new EPP server image from here:  https://www.endpointprotector.com/epp/virtual-app-email
The first link, is the Ubuntu 22.04 image,server version 5.8.1.0

2.Then deploy the EPP image using the steps from the following user manual:  https://www.endpointprotector.com/support/pdf/manual/Endpoint_Protector_Virtual_and_Hardware_Appliance-User_Manual_EN.pdf  sau de aici https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dwgqKcLpz770knOXMAgbscJpemtPtVsn/view
* If you need the logs you can create backups and download them before the migration (EPP UI > System Maintenance > Audit Log Backup).
3. Create a Snapshot of the current EPP server from the VM.
Please activate the trial license on the new server.
4. Please make sure that the EPP server version from the old server is the same as the version
of the new server. If not, update will be needed
Update the EPP server to the latest version -  (it needs to be the same as the new image).You can also check it from ""Dashboard > Live update > View applied updates"". The process is listed below

Navigate to EPP User Interface > Dashboard > Live Update > Check Now > Apply Update. Please apply one update at a time and repeat the same step until you reach version 5.6.0.0 (it can be checked in the right-bottom corner of the EPP UI). Wait for the progress bar to reach 100% and only after that you can refresh the page and continue with the next update as per below image. Please help to get the information regarding syslog on our epp server as during our today's zoom call they are not visible.
Also to meet our compliance, we want to have syslog to be stored in server for 1 year. Please check the possibility to enable that as well.
Title : RE: RE: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #411172 - - EPP version & server upgarde . Previoud ticket is 00409909    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0BVijB:ref ]
Thank you for your time during the call today.
As mentioned, I will resend over the steps.
As proposed, leave the Audit Backup to run- soon, you should find some entries at the bottom of the page, with some tarball files of the logs.
1.You can download a new EPP server image from here: https://www.endpointprotector.com/epp/virtual-app-email
The first link, is the Ubuntu 22.04 image,server version 5.8.1.0

2.Then deploy the EPP image using the steps from the following user manual: https://www.endpointprotector.com/support/pdf/manual/Endpoint_Protector_Virtual_and_Hardware_Appliance-User_Manual_EN.pdf sau de aici https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dwgqKcLpz770knOXMAgbscJpemtPtVsn/view
* If you need the logs you can create backups and download them before the migration (EPP UI > System Maintenance > Audit Log Backup).
3. Create a Snapshot of the current EPP server from the VM.
Please activate the trial license on the new server.
4. Please make sure that the EPP server version from the old server is the same as the version
of the new server. If not, update will be needed
Update the EPP server to the latest version -  (it needs to be the same as the new image).You can also check it from ""Dashboard > Live update > View applied updates"". The process is listed below

Navigate to EPP User Interface > Dashboard > Live Update > Check Now > Apply Update. Please apply one update at a time and repeat the same step until you reach version 5.6.0.0 (it can be checked in the right-bottom corner of the EPP UI). Wait for the progress bar to reach 100% and only after that you can refresh the page and continue with the next update as per below image.
Please find here the patches and the order in which to apply them in.
5. Once the servers are on the same version (the old and the new one) please go to the old server in ""System Maintenance > System backup V2"".
- name the backup and add a description.
- copy the ""System Backup Key"" to a notepad.
- click ""Yes, I saved the System Backup Key"".
- wait for the Backup to finish.

6.In the new server please go to ""System Maintenance > System backup V2"".Please note that the System Backup v2 will only backup database and other metadata without logs data, but keeping table structure.Here please:
- select the backup created in the old server
- wait for the import to finish.
7.  You will find all the computers on the new server, all the rights and all the settings, except the logs.
DLP | Device Control | Content Aware Protection | Enforced Encryption | eDiscovery

Title : RE: RE: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #411172 - - EPP version & server upgarde . Previoud ticket is 00409909    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0BVijB:ref ]
Thank you for your time during the call today.
As mentioned, I will resend over the steps.
As proposed, leave the Audit Backup to run- soon, you should find some entries at the bottom of the page, with some tarball files of the logs.
1.You can download a new EPP server image from here: https://www.endpointprotector.com/epp/virtual-app-email
The first link, is the Ubuntu 22.04 image,server version 5.8.1.0

2.Then deploy the EPP image using the steps from the following user manual: https://www.endpointprotector.com/support/pdf/manual/Endpoint_Protector_Virtual_and_Hardware_Appliance-User_Manual_EN.pdf sau de aici https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dwgqKcLpz770knOXMAgbscJpemtPtVsn/view
* If you need the logs you can create backups and download them before the migration (EPP UI > System Maintenance > Audit Log Backup).
3. Create a Snapshot of the current EPP server from the VM.
Please activate the trial license on the new server.
4. Please make sure that the EPP server version from the old server is the same as the version
of the new server. If not, update will be needed
Update the EPP server to the latest version -  (it needs to be the same as the new image).You can also check it from ""Dashboard > Live update > View applied updates"". The process is listed below

Navigate to EPP User Interface > Dashboard > Live Update > Check Now > Apply Update. Please apply one update at a time and repeat the same step until you reach version 5.6.0.0 (it can be checked in the right-bottom corner of the EPP UI). Wait for the progress bar to reach 100% and only after that you can refresh the page and continue with the next update as per below image.
Please find here the patches and the order in which to apply them in.
5. Once the servers are on the same version (the old and the new one) please go to the old server in ""System Maintenance > System backup V2"".
- name the backup and add a description.
- copy the ""System Backup Key"" to a notepad.
- click ""Yes, I saved the System Backup Key"".
- wait for the Backup to finish.

6.In the new server please go to ""System Maintenance > System backup V2"".Please note that the System Backup v2 will only backup database and other metadata without logs data, but keeping table structure.Here please:
- select the backup created in the old server
- wait for the import to finish.
7.  You will find all the computers on the new server, all the rights and all the settings, except the logs.
